com.alexgilleran.icesoap.request
Interface Request<ResultType,SOAPFaultType>

Type Parameters:
ResultType - The type of the object to retrieve from this request. If the type is a List, you may want to consider using ListRequest instead.
SOAPFaultType - The type of the fault object that will be parsed from the response, should an HTTP Error 500 be encountered.
All Known Subinterfaces:
ListRequest<ResultType,SOAPFaultType>, SOAP11ListRequest<ResultType>, SOAP11Request<ResultType>
All Known Implementing Classes:
ListRequestImpl, RequestImpl, SOAP11ListRequestImpl, SOAP11RequestImpl
public interface Request<ResultType,SOAPFaultType>

Encapsulates all the code for making a SOAP Request - to use, create an object that implements the SOAP11Observer class (generally this is easiest using anonymous objects from the activity or fragment) and attach it using the Request#registerObserver(SOAP11Observer) method. Then invoke execute() - the request will be performed on a background thread, and methods of the SOAP11Observer will be called on the UI thread.

Author:
Alex Gilleran
